1
00:00:00,795 --> 00:00:03,695
I'm in love with you, Haru-tan!

2
00:00:03,695 --> 00:00:04,612
I like you.

3
00:00:04,612 --> 00:00:06,545
Director, you can't possibly protect him.

4
00:00:06,545 --> 00:00:09,253
I made him what he is today.

5
00:00:09,253 --> 00:00:11,795
- I'm head-over-heels for you, Haruta!
- Ouch.

6
00:00:11,795 --> 00:00:15,545
A man like you, who has no consideration toward others, doesn't deserve a house mate.

7
00:00:15,545 --> 00:00:19,270
Can't we... live together as friends like before?

8
00:00:19,270 --> 00:00:21,654
Haruta, you're being unfair.

9
00:00:21,654 --> 00:00:23,395
Could you please divorce me?

10
00:00:23,395 --> 00:00:24,835
Do you have another woman?

11
00:00:24,835 --> 00:00:26,295
Who's your lover?

12
00:00:26,295 --> 00:00:27,328
Haru-tan.

13
00:00:27,328 --> 00:00:28,935
Haruka?

14
00:00:28,935 --> 00:00:31,935
You must be Soichi Haruta.

15
00:00:31,935 --> 00:00:35,240
There's something I need to ask you.

16
00:00:35,240 --> 00:00:36,860
Sure.

17
00:00:37,628 --> 00:00:39,935
Please, sit down.

18
00:00:43,980 --> 00:00:48,019
[Tenku Real Estate Co., Ltd.]

19
00:00:48,019 --> 00:00:51,260
Is there a problem?

20
00:00:51,260 --> 00:00:53,030
Sorry?

21
00:00:53,036 --> 00:00:54,028
Well...

22
00:00:54,028 --> 00:00:58,435
I'm looking for a spacious one-room apartment.

23
00:00:58,435 --> 00:01:01,662
Okay. A spacious 1LDK apartment.
(T/N: 1 bedroom, living room, dining room, and kitchen)

24
00:01:01,662 --> 00:01:05,062
- Is this for single occupancy?
- Huh?

25
00:01:05,062 --> 00:01:06,219
Sorry.

26
00:01:06,219 --> 00:01:08,286
Yes, a single resident apartment.

27
00:01:08,286 --> 00:01:10,236
I understand.

28
00:01:10,236 --> 00:01:12,340
First, please fill out this form.

29
00:01:12,340 --> 00:01:14,430
[Name | Address]

30
00:01:20,386 --> 00:01:22,710
This is the place.

31
00:01:22,710 --> 00:01:24,330
Please, come in.

32
00:01:29,035 --> 00:01:30,635
Please use these.

33
00:01:32,211 --> 00:01:35,186
It's a little far from the train station.

34
00:01:35,186 --> 00:01:37,935
However, there are many buses available at this stop.

35
00:01:37,935 --> 00:01:42,180
It's a very popular location as there's a large park nearby.

36
00:01:42,180 --> 00:01:44,630
I see.

37
00:01:46,728 --> 00:01:49,286
Where do you work?

38
00:01:49,286 --> 00:01:50,695
Why do you ask?

39
00:01:50,695 --> 00:01:55,759
Well, access to work is an important element in house-hunting.

40
00:01:55,759 --> 00:01:59,171
Yes, of course.

41
00:01:59,171 --> 00:02:02,145
A friend and I run a store.

42
00:02:02,835 --> 00:02:05,228
I drive myself to work.

43
00:02:05,228 --> 00:02:07,128
I see.

44
00:02:08,311 --> 00:02:10,936
The complex also has a shared lounge.

45
00:02:10,936 --> 00:02:15,035
Many tenants are singles, so there's a lot of interaction.

46
00:02:15,035 --> 00:02:18,786
- Like that reality TV show?
- Exactly, like the show about the nursing home.

47
00:02:18,795 --> 00:02:20,995
What?

48
00:02:20,995 --> 00:02:22,520
Sorry, wrong choice of words.

49
00:02:22,520 --> 00:02:24,453
Can you show me other options?

50
00:02:24,453 --> 00:02:25,920
Yes, of course.

51
00:02:25,920 --> 00:02:28,440
[Tenku Real Estate Co., Ltd.]

52
00:02:33,770 --> 00:02:36,620
[Masamune Takekawa | Sales Department Supervisor]

53
00:02:36,623 --> 00:02:38,403
Haruta!

54
00:02:38,403 --> 00:02:41,845
He must be out.

55
00:02:41,845 --> 00:02:44,403
He's out with a client. Is there any problem?

56
00:02:44,403 --> 00:02:46,270
Look at this.

57
00:02:46,270 --> 00:02:48,487
Oh, no! It's the Director's wife.

58
00:02:48,487 --> 00:02:49,528
She's back again.

59
00:02:49,528 --> 00:02:53,787
She's looking for a single residence apartment?

60
00:02:53,787 --> 00:02:54,835
Bingo!

61
00:02:54,835 --> 00:02:55,878
Separation! Divorce!

62
00:02:55,878 --> 00:02:57,645
No, he would never divorce her.

63
00:02:57,645 --> 00:02:59,070
- Mid-life crisis!
- Never!

64
00:02:59,070 --> 00:03:02,912
- Everyone, big news!
- Don't yell. We don't know that for sure.

65
00:03:02,912 --> 00:03:04,936
He's divorcing her?

66
00:03:04,936 --> 00:03:07,735
The next one is just around the corner.

67
00:03:07,735 --> 00:03:09,812
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

68
00:03:09,812 --> 00:03:11,978
You've been saying that for a while.

69
00:03:11,978 --> 00:03:13,311
- Excuse me.
- Yes?

70
00:03:13,311 --> 00:03:17,420
Where is North Musashino Community Hall?

71
00:03:17,420 --> 00:03:20,311
North Musashino Community Hall?

72
00:03:20,311 --> 00:03:22,654
You'll need to go to the main road over there.

73
00:03:22,654 --> 00:03:25,353
Then turn left and walk to the bus stop.

74
00:03:25,353 --> 00:03:27,435
From there...

75
00:03:27,435 --> 00:03:32,145
take bus No. 72 to the Astronomical Science Center.

76
00:03:32,145 --> 00:03:34,425
How about I escort you there?

77
00:03:34,425 --> 00:03:36,735
Sorry. Could you wait a little?

78
00:03:36,735 --> 00:03:38,378
I'll be right back.

79
00:03:38,378 --> 00:03:40,120
Let's go, Granny.

80
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:43,328
Stay here, I'll be right back.

81
00:03:46,420 --> 00:03:48,735
Soichi Haruta.

82
00:03:48,735 --> 00:03:51,035
[Hobby: Sleeping]

83
00:03:51,035 --> 00:03:52,936
[Characteristics: Kind-hearted]

84
00:03:56,554 --> 00:03:59,086
What a splendid view!

85
00:03:59,086 --> 00:04:00,910
What's that over there?

86
00:04:00,910 --> 00:04:04,360
- It looks like a big rock.
- I wonder.

87
00:04:05,835 --> 00:04:08,028
- Hey, tell me.
- Yes?

88
00:04:08,028 --> 00:04:12,119
- Is there a girl named Haruka in your office?
- What?

89
00:04:12,119 --> 00:04:13,795
Haruka!

90
00:04:13,795 --> 00:04:15,712
Ms. Haruka?

91
00:04:15,712 --> 00:04:18,895
There's nobody by this name at our branch.

92
00:04:21,228 --> 00:04:26,511
Can you check if she works at the headquarters?

93
00:04:26,511 --> 00:04:30,835
Sure. Is this someone you know?

94
00:04:31,735 --> 00:04:36,254
I heard my friend's daughter works at the agency.

95
00:04:36,254 --> 00:04:40,211
She's had a baby, so I want to send her a gift.

96
00:04:40,211 --> 00:04:43,935
Of course. What's her surname?

97
00:04:44,735 --> 00:04:48,535
I don't know. It changed when she married.

98
00:04:48,535 --> 00:04:49,936
I see.

99
00:04:49,936 --> 00:04:51,735
Okay. I'll look into it.

100
00:04:51,735 --> 00:04:52,654
Thank you.

101
00:04:52,654 --> 00:04:55,078
It's Haruka, right?

102
00:04:57,478 --> 00:04:58,945
At that moment,

103
00:04:58,945 --> 00:05:03,630
I had no idea I was stepping into

104
00:05:03,630 --> 00:05:05,361
a bloodcurdling divorce drama.

105
00:05:05,361 --> 00:05:09,935
[Ossan's Love]

106
00:05:11,687 --> 00:05:15,400
[Episode 3: What's Your Name?]

107
00:05:15,911 --> 00:05:19,490
[Musashi Korosawa | Sales Department Director]

108
00:05:23,019 --> 00:05:26,695
Stop fighting over me!

109
00:05:27,280 --> 00:05:31,530
Thanks to your effort during the previous campaign,

110
00:05:31,535 --> 00:05:35,680
we were able to achieve our goals successfully.

111
00:05:37,186 --> 00:05:39,735
The headquarters has recommended us to many properties.

112
00:05:39,735 --> 00:05:45,019
I would like to focus on condos for singles and solo residents.

113
00:05:45,019 --> 00:05:49,035
Both terms sound so lonely.

114
00:05:49,035 --> 00:05:50,695
Such properties usually allow pets.

115
00:05:50,695 --> 00:05:52,512
Having a pet makes you single for life.

116
00:05:52,512 --> 00:05:57,678
We'll focus our campaign on working women in office buildings.

117
00:05:57,678 --> 00:06:00,503
- Maro, be our sandwich man.
- Sandwich man?

118
00:06:00,503 --> 00:06:02,670
- Haruta, keep him company.
- Okay.

119
00:06:02,670 --> 00:06:06,061
Sandwich man? Which guy should I play?

120
00:06:06,061 --> 00:06:09,253
What do you mean? It's not the famous comedy duo.

121
00:06:11,612 --> 00:06:15,835
- I don't get you.
- Come on. Admit your mistake.

122
00:06:15,835 --> 00:06:17,378
No comeback?

123
00:06:17,378 --> 00:06:20,295
Haruta, can you organize a celebratory party for the campaign?

124
00:06:20,295 --> 00:06:23,445
Sure, I'll let you know when I find a venue.

125
00:06:23,445 --> 00:06:25,420
- I'm counting on you.
- Yes.

126
00:06:33,310 --> 00:06:35,011
Sorry.

127
00:06:41,936 --> 00:06:43,558
- How did it go?
- Tell me.

128
00:06:43,558 --> 00:06:44,635
What are you talking about?

129
00:06:44,635 --> 00:06:47,435
You showed her apartments, right?

130
00:06:47,435 --> 00:06:50,211
Yes, a few spacious 1LDK apartments.

131
00:06:50,211 --> 00:06:52,745
- What was she like?
- What?

132
00:06:53,462 --> 00:06:56,835
She's a nice lady, very frank and open.

133
00:06:56,835 --> 00:07:03,435
A typical hard-working career lady who missed out on marriage.

134
00:07:03,435 --> 00:07:06,712
No, she's a married woman.

135
00:07:06,712 --> 00:07:09,845
- What?
- She is the Director's wife.

136
00:07:09,845 --> 00:07:13,295
- Say what? Is she Director's...?
- Exactly.

137
00:07:13,295 --> 00:07:16,235
- Was there any mention of divorce?
- What?

138
00:07:16,235 --> 00:07:17,835
I asked my wife for a divorce.

139
00:07:17,835 --> 00:07:21,078
So please give me a little more time.

140
00:07:21,078 --> 00:07:22,311
Am I the cause?

141
00:07:22,311 --> 00:07:24,045
The Director must be having an affair.

142
00:07:24,045 --> 00:07:26,328
He's committed adultery?

143
00:07:26,328 --> 00:07:27,966
What an ugly mess! Yeah!

144
00:07:27,966 --> 00:07:30,386
Who the hell is his mistress?

145
00:07:30,386 --> 00:07:35,835
Don't tell me... she works at this branch.

146
00:07:35,835 --> 00:07:38,554
Is there a girl named Haruka in your office?

147
00:07:38,554 --> 00:07:41,086
There's nobody by this name at our branch.

148
00:07:41,086 --> 00:07:42,153
It's me.

149
00:07:42,153 --> 00:07:43,836
For your information, it's not me.

150
00:07:43,836 --> 00:07:47,960
Anyway, Haruta. Don't make it any worse.

151
00:07:47,960 --> 00:07:49,520
Okay.

152
00:07:51,570 --> 00:07:53,211
Seriously?

153
00:07:53,211 --> 00:07:58,936
Helping her find an apartment means supporting their divorce?

154
00:08:04,035 --> 00:08:08,036
- Maki, what do I do?
- I have no idea. Leave me alone.

155
00:08:09,835 --> 00:08:12,528
We can never go back to how we used to be.

156
00:08:13,503 --> 00:08:17,210
Good. You're back to your usual self.

157
00:08:17,210 --> 00:08:18,690
What?

158
00:08:19,460 --> 00:08:23,403
- Maki, got a minute?
- Yes.

159
00:08:26,935 --> 00:08:28,962
You haven't updated this.

160
00:08:28,962 --> 00:08:30,735
- Right.
- Why haven't you?

161
00:08:30,735 --> 00:08:33,303
- Sorry.
- Answer the question.

162
00:08:33,303 --> 00:08:35,220
I'll do it right away. What do you want?

163
00:08:36,520 --> 00:08:40,978
What's with you? Snap out of it.

164
00:08:44,936 --> 00:08:46,828
Good work, everyone!

165
00:08:46,828 --> 00:08:50,210
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

166
00:08:51,087 --> 00:08:52,720
Where's the Director?

167
00:08:52,720 --> 00:08:54,336
He's not coming. Some last minute thing.

168
00:08:54,336 --> 00:08:59,028
I suppose he's having a problem with his wife.

169
00:08:59,028 --> 00:09:00,728
You sound so happy.

170
00:09:00,728 --> 00:09:02,145
Haruta, go order spicy cod innards.

171
00:09:02,145 --> 00:09:04,403
Why me?

172
00:09:04,403 --> 00:09:05,687
You're the organizer, right?

173
00:09:05,687 --> 00:09:07,735
Yes, but... you get on my nerves!

174
00:09:07,735 --> 00:09:09,186
- Carry on, then.
- I said, okay.

175
00:09:09,186 --> 00:09:11,795
Maki takes care of chores at home, right?

176
00:09:11,795 --> 00:09:14,735
No, I do my own chores.

177
00:09:14,735 --> 00:09:17,321
- What are you talking about?
- They're house mates.

178
00:09:17,321 --> 00:09:18,503
Yes, we are.

179
00:09:18,503 --> 00:09:20,612
Really? Like peas in a pod.

180
00:09:20,612 --> 00:09:23,211
It sounds like fun.

181
00:09:24,728 --> 00:09:27,728
I envy your youth.

182
00:09:28,628 --> 00:09:30,103
Maki.

183
00:09:30,103 --> 00:09:31,778
Teppei, can I place an order?

184
00:09:31,778 --> 00:09:33,061
- Sure.
- What kind of curry is that?

185
00:09:33,061 --> 00:09:36,554
It's sour curry. I added lemon, pickled plums, and vinegar.

186
00:09:36,554 --> 00:09:40,735
It's a carnival of spiciness and sourness in your mouth.

187
00:09:40,735 --> 00:09:43,119
Okay, I'll have chitterlings stew and spicy cod innards.

188
00:09:43,119 --> 00:09:44,919
Got it.

189
00:09:46,320 --> 00:09:48,835
There we go again. You're showing off how exhausted you are.

190
00:09:48,835 --> 00:09:50,303
I'm not.

191
00:09:50,303 --> 00:09:54,611
The Director's wife came to the office today.

192
00:09:54,611 --> 00:09:56,128
Did she find out about you and Director?

193
00:09:56,128 --> 00:09:59,870
No, he asked for a divorce, but she doesn't know the reason.

194
00:09:59,870 --> 00:10:03,495
Well, he can't spill all the beans.

195
00:10:03,495 --> 00:10:05,386
- Meaning?
- Because...

196
00:10:05,386 --> 00:10:10,653
telling her means he's coming out of the closet.

197
00:10:10,653 --> 00:10:11,735
Right.

198
00:10:11,735 --> 00:10:15,595
- That's far more devastating than an ordinary adultery.
- Indeed.

199
00:10:15,595 --> 00:10:19,554
Moreover, he's in love with you. That's devastating, all right.

200
00:10:19,554 --> 00:10:21,135
Don't rub it in.

201
00:10:21,135 --> 00:10:24,261
She would be devastating, for sure.

202
00:10:24,261 --> 00:10:26,378
Say something.

203
00:10:35,061 --> 00:10:38,595
Why can't you answer me?

204
00:10:43,628 --> 00:10:45,128
I'm sorry.

205
00:10:47,978 --> 00:10:51,935
All I want is the reason for our divorce.

206
00:10:51,935 --> 00:10:54,308
What did I do wrong?

207
00:10:55,562 --> 00:10:57,286
It's not your fault.

208
00:10:57,286 --> 00:10:59,250
Then why?

209
00:11:02,645 --> 00:11:05,072
You're in love with another woman?

210
00:11:06,109 --> 00:11:09,270
No, it's not a woman.

211
00:11:09,270 --> 00:11:11,835
It has to be!

212
00:11:11,835 --> 00:11:13,335
No, it's not.

213
00:11:18,645 --> 00:11:24,335
Then what do you make of our 30 years of marriage?

214
00:11:25,835 --> 00:11:30,912
I have always believed a married couple could tell each other everything,

215
00:11:34,835 --> 00:11:37,735
but if you refuse to tell me the truth,

216
00:11:37,735 --> 00:11:42,387
I'll have no choice but to hire a private detective.

217
00:11:43,170 --> 00:11:46,019
Choko, don't do that.

218
00:11:46,019 --> 00:11:51,412
You expect me to agree to a divorce without any explanation?

219
00:11:52,061 --> 00:11:57,110
I'm not that naive.

220
00:11:58,735 --> 00:12:01,395
We'll need to divide up all our assets.

221
00:12:02,362 --> 00:12:04,535
I...

222
00:12:06,835 --> 00:12:08,561
Even I...

223
00:12:09,935 --> 00:12:12,053
have my pride.

224
00:12:20,712 --> 00:12:22,154
The thing is...

225
00:12:24,228 --> 00:12:25,770
I...

226
00:12:28,935 --> 00:12:30,535
To be honest...

227
00:12:32,670 --> 00:12:34,270
I...

228
00:12:40,353 --> 00:12:42,735
Sorry for the wait.

229
00:12:42,735 --> 00:12:44,462
Thank you.

230
00:12:44,462 --> 00:12:45,986
Looks good.

231
00:12:45,986 --> 00:12:47,966
Haruta, clear the empty glasses.

232
00:12:47,966 --> 00:12:49,949
Don't boss me around. I'm a customer.

233
00:12:49,949 --> 00:12:51,958
Are you two dating?

234
00:12:51,958 --> 00:12:55,603
No, we're just childhood friends.

235
00:12:55,603 --> 00:12:56,835
You'll end up together.

236
00:12:56,835 --> 00:12:59,735
Not a chance. I'm into young girls with big boobs.

237
00:12:59,735 --> 00:13:00,736
So you say.

238
00:13:00,736 --> 00:13:04,320
But in the end, you'll marry your childhood friend.

239
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:06,612
That will never happen.

240
00:13:06,612 --> 00:13:08,735
Well, then.

241
00:13:08,735 --> 00:13:13,135
- Do you mind if I make a move on you?
- What?

242
00:13:13,135 --> 00:13:14,835
I have to say,

243
00:13:14,835 --> 00:13:17,436
your face is my ideal type.

244
00:13:17,436 --> 00:13:21,128
Thanks. I thrive on praise.

245
00:13:21,128 --> 00:13:24,935
Okay then, can we exchange our contact information?

246
00:13:24,935 --> 00:13:26,487
- For real?
- Yes.

247
00:13:26,487 --> 00:13:28,095
Sure.

248
00:13:28,095 --> 00:13:30,411
- Just shake your phone.
- Shake? Like this?

249
00:13:30,411 --> 00:13:33,545
- Where's Maki?
- He went outside with Takekawa earlier.

250
00:13:33,545 --> 00:13:35,990
Do you think he's getting a scolding?

251
00:13:35,990 --> 00:13:38,640
- Did you get it?
- Not yet.

252
00:13:40,487 --> 00:13:42,536
That all it was.

253
00:13:44,712 --> 00:13:47,253
That's not a good enough explanation!

254
00:13:48,528 --> 00:13:50,135
I'm sorry.

255
00:13:50,735 --> 00:13:52,986
Do you think that's acceptable?

256
00:13:52,986 --> 00:13:54,295
I mean...

257
00:13:54,295 --> 00:13:55,895
Speak up.

258
00:13:57,935 --> 00:13:59,735
You can take a bath first.

259
00:13:59,735 --> 00:14:01,728
Okay, thanks.

260
00:14:06,019 --> 00:14:07,861
What was that about earlier?

261
00:14:07,861 --> 00:14:09,445
What do you mean?

262
00:14:09,445 --> 00:14:12,554
Takekawa was grilling you outside.

263
00:14:13,854 --> 00:14:15,119
No big deal.

264
00:14:15,119 --> 00:14:16,936
What's the matter?

265
00:14:16,936 --> 00:14:19,919
We're close friends. You can talk to me.

266
00:14:19,919 --> 00:14:22,320
Thanks, but I'm good.

267
